- merge trees rooted at a and b, return merged tree root - $\text{key}_a &lt; \text{key}_b \quad \forall a \in A, b \in B$  - implicit treap? - No Change, why? <pre><code>Node* merge(Node* a, Node* b) //key a &lt; key b
{
    if (!a) return b; //base case
    if (!b) return a;
    if(a−&gt;pri &gt; b−&gt;pri)//pri a bigger =&gt; a as root
    {
        a−&gt;r = merge(a−&gt;r, b); //key b bigger =&gt; merge b and rc of a
        return a;
    }
    //b as root
    b−&gt;l = merge(a, b−&gt;l); //key a smaller =&gt; merge a and lc of b
    return b;
}
</code></pre> <p>Note: - Merge preserve BST order, so when still work on implicit key</p>

